&lt;p&gt;As &lt;strong&gt;Commercial Finance Manager – Channels and Partnerships&lt;/strong&gt;, you will be a strategic finance partner to Channel Sales, Partnerships and Product leadership teams for Convera’s partner-led growth motions, including indirect channels, strategic alliances, embedded finance and distribution partnerships.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your mission is to &lt;strong&gt;improve commercial decision‑making&lt;/strong&gt;—from pricing and deal structuring to customer profitability and growth investment tradeoffs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role reports to Head of Commercial Finance (Partners and Channels) and sits at the intersection of &lt;strong&gt;finance, strategy, and execution&lt;/strong&gt;. You’ll translate data into insight, insight into action, and action into measurable financial impact.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Business Partnership &amp;amp; Decision Support&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Sales, Partnerships, Revenue Operations, Marketing and Product leaders to evaluate partner strategies, growth initiatives, commercial structures and commercial investments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the primary finance thought partner for key commercial decisions, ensuring alignment with financial objectives, incentive design and risk tolerance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Challenge assumptions, pressure‑test proposals, and help leaders understand tradeoffs between growth, margin, and risk&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Commercial Performance &amp;amp; Insights&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own customer, product, and channel profitability analysis, identifying drivers of performance and actionable improvement opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain key commercial KPIs (e.g., revenue quality, partner contribution, deal economics, cost-to-serve, margin, customer acquisition economics, retention, LTV/CAC)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create clear, executive‑ready narratives explaining what’s happening in the business and why&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pricing, Deals &amp;amp; Investment Economics&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support pricing strategy, revenue share arrangements and commercial terms to drive disciplined and repeatable deal outcomes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build financial models for new partnerships, channel launches and embedded or indirect GTM initiatives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate ROI on commercial investments and recommend course corrections as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Planning, Forecasting &amp;amp; Governance&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support revenue forecasting and scenario analysis, incorporating commercial risks and opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with the broader Finance function to ensure forecasts, plans, and incentives reflect economic reality&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help embed governance processes that balance speed with financial discipline&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Enablement &amp;amp; Finance Excellence&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Improve commercial and financial understanding across partner‑facing teams—setting the standard for data‑driven decision‑making&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate complex analyses into simple tools, models, and dashboards for non‑finance stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coach and mentor junior team members, contributing to the development of a high‑performing Commercial Finance function&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What Success Looks Like&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Commercial leaders proactively seek you out for partnership on critical decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Better pricing, deal quality, and customer mix lead to measurable margin improvement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Forecasts are more accurate, risks are surfaced earlier, and surprises are reduced&lt;/li&gt;
